The course is aimed at graduate students and researchers with some statistical knowledge; ideally you'll know something about generalized linear models, likelihood, and AIC. However we?ll recap what GLMs are so if you?re a little rusty or not everything mentioned in the GLM course makes sense, we have you covered. From running the course previously, knowing the difference between "fixed" and "random" effects, and what the terms "random intercepts" and "random slopes" are, will be helpful for the Hierarchical GAM topic, but we don't expect you to be an expert in mixed effects or hierarchical models to take this course.
